result.execSummary:
The defendant Willie Frank Helgeson was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Retail Theft - Intentionally Take (<=$500), a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.50(1m)(b).
  • Retail Theft - Intentionally Take (<=$500), a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.50(1m)(b).
  • Retail Theft - Intentionally Take (<=$500), a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.50(1m)(b).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Willie Frank Helgeson in court with attorney Danielle L. Shelton.  Defendant Willie Frank Helgeson in custody.  Alex T. Mueller appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy court clerk cmt.
Defendant prepared to enter change of plea.  Hearing proceeded.  Negotiations set forth by the state.

As to Counts 1, 2, 3:  Defendant changes his plea to GUILTY.  Defendant examined as to his plea, advised of his Constitutional rights and the maximum penalty.   Defendant advised that if not a United States Citizen, deportation is possible.  Court found that defendant knowingly, voluntarily and intelligently waived his rights.  Guilty Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights and Addendum received and filed.  Parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis to sustain defendant's plea.  Court found defendant guilty and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered on the record.

As to Count 4:  Pursuant to plea negotiations and on State's motion, Court orders Count 4 dismissed but read-in for purposes of sentencing.  

Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by parties.  
As to Count 1:  Defendant ordered to serve 4 months in the House of Correction consecutive to any other sentence with credit of 67 days time served, and with release for the Day Reporting Center.

As to Count 2:  Defendant ordered to serve 4 months in the House of Correction consecutive to Counts 1 and 3, and with release for the Day Reporting Center.

As to Count 3:  Defendant ordered to serve 4 months in the House of Correction consecutive to Counts 1 and 2, and with release for the Day Reporting Center.

Court ordered defendant to pay restitution to Roundy's Supermarkets Inc. in the amount of $386.00 by 12-11-2017 or civil judgment.  
Court ordered defendant to pay all costs, fees and surcharges by 12-11-2017 or civil judgment.  Restitution to be paid first.
